Six aid workers are kidnapped in Yemen's Al Mahwit Governorate. (CNN)A Libyan military court sentences a group of Russian, Belarussian and Ukrainian men to long prison terms, having found them guilty of serving as mercenaries for Muammar Gaddafi in the Libyan Civil War. A Russian who was deemed the group's leader was sentenced to life imprisonment, and the rest were sentenced to 10 years in prison with hard labor. (Reuters)There are widespread reports of at least 92 people being killed in the village of Houla in Syria Homs Governorate. (Agencies via The Canberra Times)